### Milestone 7 — Tiered adaptive fallback (v5 stream)

Currently the adaptive encoder has two outcomes for a ClassNormal ratio:
  - Pass ε at 16 bits → uint16 (2 bytes)
  - Fail → ClassNormalExact → float64 (8 bytes)

This skips the u32 tier entirely. Adding a middle tier:
  - Pass ε at 16 bits → ClassNormal16 → uint16 (2 bytes)   [renamed from ClassNormal]
  - Fail at 16 bits, pass ε at 30 bits → ClassNormal32 → uint32 (4 bytes)   [new]
  - Fail at 30 bits → ClassNormalExact → float64 (8 bytes)

Benefit: ratios that resist 16-bit quantization but pass 30-bit cost 4 bytes
instead of 8. Win band: ε values roughly 1e-6 to 1e-4 (tight-tolerance use cases).
Fast path (delta16 < tol) unchanged — still skips all checks for common case.

